name: Cldr.Format.Date

unions.name: FormatType
unions.comment:
Dates can be formatted using a
`Cldr.Format.Length.Length` or `Cldr.Format.Options.DateOptions`.

values.name: format

name: Cldr.Format.DateTime

unions.name: FormatType
unions.comment: The different combinations of date and time that can be formatted.

values.name: format
values.comment:
Format a `Time.Posix` value, using the format for a specified `FormatType`, `Locale`, and `Time.Zone`

    import Time
    import Cldr.Locale exposing (en)

    format short en Time.utc (Time.millisToPosix 959829796738)
    --> "6/1/00, 3:23 AM"

values.name: full
values.comment: Use `Full` for both date and time

values.name: long
values.comment: Use `Long` for both date and time

values.name: medium
values.comment: Use `Medium` for both date and time

values.name: short
values.comment: Use `Short` for both date and time

name: Cldr.Format.Length

unions.name: Length
unions.comment:
There are four lengths for formatting.
These determine how verbose the formatted output will be.

name: Cldr.Format.Options

unions.name: FractionalDigits
unions.comment: A value to choose the number of fractional digits to display.

unions.name: HourType
unions.comment: A value to choose between 12 and 24 hour based formatting.

unions.name: NameOption
unions.comment: Time Zone names can only be "short" or "long".

unions.name: NumberOption
unions.comment: A value for number-based options, such as year or hour.

unions.name: NumberOrTextOption
unions.comment: A value for options that can use text or numbers, such as month.

unions.name: TextOption
unions.comment: A value for text-based options, such as weekday name and am/pm period.

aliases.name: DateOptions
aliases.comment:
The options that are relevant to formatting a Date value.

These match a subset of the options that can be used in the
[`Intl.DateTimeFormat`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/DateTimeFormat/DateTimeFormat) JS [API](https://402.ecma-international.org/8.0/#table-datetimeformat-components).

name: Cldr.Locale

Represents the locale to use for formatting.

You can parse a value from JS like `navigator.language` or use hardcoded locales.
